Financial markets have performed at an all-time high in the past decade, yet systemic shifts and technological disruption loom large on the horizon. So what can make markets more resilient for the future?


CNBC's Geoff Cutmore leads the discussion from Davos with U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin, U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer Sajid Javid, IMF Managing Director Kristalina Georgieva and UBS Chairman Axel Weber. #WEF20...